latestPosts.caption:
✈️Las Vegas with Kids: 3-Day Family-Friendly Itinerary. 📍Save this🩷

We just got back from an unforgettable family trip to Las Vegas with our 9-year-old planned around the 🩷Coldplay concert🩷,and YES—there’s so much to do with kids beyond the casinos and nightlife! From immersive art to first concerts, dancing fountains to virtual reality, here’s how we made core memories on the Strip:

Day 1: Mind-Bending Fun at AREA15 + Sweet Treats

✔️ @bellagio Conservatory & Botanical Gardens – vibrant, seasonal displays (free!)
✔️ @area15official & @meow__wolf Omega Mart.A wild, immersive art installation filled with hidden passageways, surreal storytelling, and interactive exhibits. Perfect for curious kids and adults alike! Plan 2–3 hours here. ✔️ M&MWorld + Hershey’s Chocolate World – both free and full of sweet fun ✔️ Coca-Cola Store – grab fun international flavors (optional tasting tray)

Day 2: Ocean Life, Lights & Legendary Dance
➡️Morning at Shark Reef Aquarium @mandalaybay  ➡️Walk-through tunnel, sharks, rays, and reptiles—cool and fun!
➡️Afternoon Tram Ride + LINQ Promenade ➡️Took the free Las Vegas trams between resorts ➡️Strolled through LINQ Promenade—a fun, walkable strip with shops and activities ➡️Tried a VR experience inside one of the LINQ stores—super fun for our son! Check out the shops and eateries 
➡️Dinner at Promenade 
➡️Evening at Bellagio:Fountain Show – music, lights, water magic!

Day 3: Pool Time + shows across the strip

🩷Morning: Chill time by the hotel pool 
🩷Flamingo Wildlife Habitat
🩷Fall of Atlantis Show (Caesars)
🩷Mirage Volcano Show (check schedule)
Evening : @jabbawockeez Dance Show (MGM Grand). High-energy, family-friendly performance with visuals, humor, and incredible moves! Must-watch.

💖Tips for Vegas With Kids:
* Hydrate often—Vegas heat is no joke
* Book your top experiences early
* Plan for downtime between big activities
* Use trams + walk indoors to beat the heat
* Let your kids help choose one activity per day!

#FamilyVegasTrip #KidFriendlyVegas #OmegaMart #Jabbawockeez #LINQPromenade #VegasFamilyGuide #FamilyTravel #VegasWithKids #SummerTravel

How to keep your 🐶pup happy and make time for work, errands, or mom life this summer? ✨ @roverdotcom has been our go-to solution for years!  #roverpartner

I used Rover for our previous pet Rio and now for Astro—and it’s been a total lifesaver. We’ve found incredible sitters who genuinely love and care for him like family. No kennels or crates—just cozy, loving homes where he gets attention, playtime, and cuddles all day. 💛

What makes Rover stand out?
✔️ 5-star sitters with verified reviews
✔️ Enhanced background checks
✔️ Reservation protection
✔️ 24/7 support for pet parents + sitters
✔️ Meet & greets to find the perfect match
✔️ Emergency vet care covered under the Rover Guarantee
✔️ Services for every need—boarding, daycare, drop-ins, dog walking, and more
Astro always comes home happy and tired—and I get peace of mind knowing he’s in trusted hands while we tackle a packed summer schedule.

Check out @roverdotcom to find a loving sitter near you 🩷

#dogmom #furbaby #petsofinstagram #houstonmoms #boymomlife #summer2025

Still buzzing from an unforgettable night in Las Vegas—our first family trip to the city and our son’s first-ever concert… and it just happened to be @coldplay . 🎶💛

Watching his eyes light up as the lights, music, and crowd came alive around him was truly magical. At 9 years old, Music of Spheres was more than a concert—it was a core memory in the making.

As Coldplay nears the end of their touring journey, this show felt even more meaningful. Sharing it together as a family, singing along to the songs we love, and experiencing their energy live—it’s something we’ll all remember forever. 🌈💫

From the flight in to the final encore, Vegas gave us everything we hoped for and more. This moment? One for the books. 🫶🎤✨

#ColdplayConcert #ColdplayLive #coldplay #lasvegaswithkids #corememories #boymomlife #travelingwithkids

latestPosts.caption:
The last few days of May were full of milestones, memories, and major proud mom moments! 💫

Vir wrapped up 3rd grade as an Honor Roll student, and we couldn’t be more proud—especially after adjusting to a brand new school, building new friendships, and thriving through it all. 💛

He also ended his baseball season as an All Star—such a proud moment watching his hard work and confidence grow on the field. ⚾️🌟Vir got to be part of the on-field parade at an Astros game and walked with his grandad (a total dream!)

May was extra special because our boy also turned 9! Can’t believe how fast time is flying—but so grateful for the kind, curious kid he’s becoming. 🥹💙

We’re soaking in the start of summer the best way we know how:
📚 Stocked up on books from the library,
🧳 Now packing for our first post-school getaway of summer!

Here’s to slowing down, showing up, and making space for all the simple joys summer brings. ☀️

latestPosts.caption:
Tired of dull, faded strands but not ready for permanent color? Here’s your sign to try a HAIR GLAZE. I get one every 2-3 months.💕

I just got a hair glaze refresh — it deepened my dull strands, added shine, and gave my hair that healthy, rich tone without damaging it. It’s like a tinted top coat for your hair — no commitment, no harsh chemicals, just glow!

Why I chose glaze > dye:
* It’s ammonia-free and gentle on the hair
* Boosts shine + corrects faded color
* Ideal between salon visits
* Fades gradually, no harsh grow-out lines
* Perfect for summer hair revivals!

Whether you’re between color sessions or just want a subtle refresh before events, a glaze is the low-maintenance hair hero you didn’t know you needed.

Ask your stylist for a customized glaze — with or without pigment. Trust me, it’s magic. It took me max 20-30mins at the salon and was under $50 with Tip included. 
.
.
.

We’re always coming back to @dagamahtx it’s one of our favorite restaurants in Houston, and the perfect spot to celebrate Mother’s Day! We recently went for brunch with my in laws. 

This vibrant space overlooking the MKT trail serves fine casual Indian canteen food with a modern twist — think tandoori roots, cocktails, natural wines, and amazing plant-based options. I love the outdoor seating as well. 

Here’s what we ordered this time (and loved!):
💖Vada Pav (Vir’s go-to!)
🩷Three-Chilli Paneer
💖Masala Egg Paratha
💖Disco Egg Pao
💖Queijo Da Gama
💖Maracuja Spritz from their new brunch menu
💖& our must-haves every time: Berry Nimbu Pani & Tandoori Roots😋

Highly recommend making a reservation for Mother’s Day weekend!
